                <note rend="inline" type="source">352.1153 St 2/104: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hammond</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San Sebastian</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-08-24T15:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 24, 1928—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 24—2:39 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>78. Referring to my telegram number 59, June 9, 11 a.m.<note n="41"
                        xml:id="d735fn41">Not printed.</note> I am informed by Wescott, Shell
                    representative, that he has been instructed to accept a settlement of company’s
                    claims for expropriations on the basis of actual physical valuation, plus eight
                    per cent, plus legal interest from date of seizure. The Shell group has
                    renounced its endeavors to obtain compensation for good will and settlement on
                    more favorable exchange basis.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hammond</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
